<h1>Document Upload System</h1>
<p><strong>Project:</strong> University Admissions Portal — SafeX Solutions<br>
<strong>Developer:</strong> Group 21 Member<br>
<strong>Stack:</strong> React 19 + Express.js + SQLite (pluggable database)</p>

<hr>

<h2>What It Does</h2>
<p>Lets university applicants upload transcripts, CNIC, and photos for admission. Files are validated (type + size) and stored directly in the database — no file system needed.</p>

<hr>

<h2>How to Run</h2>
<ol>
<li><strong>Backend:</strong> <code>cd backend && npm install && npm start</code> → runs on <code>http://localhost:5000</code></li>
<li><strong>Frontend:</strong> <code>cd frontend && npm install && npm run dev</code> → runs on <code>http://localhost:3000</code></li>
<li>Open <code>http://localhost:3000</code>, enter Applicant ID, pick a file, upload</li>
</ol>

<hr>

<h2>API Endpoints</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Method</th><th>Path</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr><td>POST</td><td><code>/api/documents/upload</code></td><td>Upload a file (multipart: file + applicant_id + document_type)</td></tr>
<tr><td>GET</td><td><code>/api/documents?applicant_id=</code></td><td>List documents for an applicant</td></tr>
<tr><td>GET</td><td><code>/api/documents/:id</code></td><td>Get document metadata</td></tr>
<tr><td>GET</td><td><code>/api/documents/:id/download</code></td><td>Download the actual file from database</td></tr>
<tr><td>DELETE</td><td><code>/api/documents/:id</code></td><td>Delete a document</td></tr>
<tr><td>PATCH</td><td><code>/api/documents/:id/status</code></td><td>Update status (pending/verified/rejected)</td></tr>
</table>

<hr>

<h2>How to Integrate Into an Existing Site</h2>

<h3>Backend (3 lines of code)</h3>
<pre>const docUpload = require('./backend');
await docUpload.initDatabase();
app.use('/api/documents', docUpload.createModule());
app.use(docUpload.errorHandler);</pre>
<p>That's it. The module adds all 6 endpoints under <code>/api/documents</code>.</p>

<h3>Use Your Own Database</h3>
<p>Pass a custom repository adapter:</p>
<pre>const myRepo = {
  insertDocument: (id, applicantId, docType, fileName, fileBuffer, fileSize, mimeType) => { /* SQL */ },
  findDocuments: (applicantId) => { /* SQL query returning array */ },
  findDocumentById: (id) => { /* SQL returning one row */ },
  findDocumentFileById: (id) => { /* SQL returning {file_name, mime_type, file_data} */ },
  deleteDocumentById: (id) => { /* SQL DELETE */ },
  updateDocumentStatus: (id, status) => { /* SQL UPDATE */ },
};
app.use('/api/documents', docUpload.createModule({ repository: myRepo }));</pre>
<p>Works with PostgreSQL, MySQL, MongoDB, or any database you already have.</p>

<h3>Frontend (React)</h3>
<pre>import { DocumentUpload, DocumentList, createApiClient, useDocuments } from './frontend/src/index';
import './frontend/src/App.css';

const api = createApiClient('https://your-site.com/api/documents');

function MyPage() {
  const [id, setId] = useState('APP-2024-001');
  const { documents, deleteDocument, refresh } = useDocuments(api, id);

  return (
    &lt;div&gt;
      &lt;DocumentUpload apiClient={api} applicantId={id} onUploadSuccess={refresh} /&gt;
      &lt;DocumentList documents={documents} onDelete={deleteDocument} /&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  );
}</pre>

<hr>

<h2>Project Structure</h2>
<pre>
backend/
  config/          - Environment config + database init
  middleware/      - File upload (Multer) + error handling
  routes/          - API route definitions
  controllers/     - Request handlers
  services/        - Business logic
  db/              - Repository (database adapter)
  index.js         - Module factory (mount into any Express app)
  server.js        - Standalone launcher

frontend/
  src/
    components/    - DocumentUpload + DocumentList (reusable widgets)
    hooks/         - useDocuments (API state hook)
    api.js         - API client factory
    index.js       - Public exports
    App.jsx        - Demo app
    App.css        - Scoped styles
</pre>

<hr>

<h2>Challenges Faced</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>No Python on machine:</strong> Native SQLite modules (better-sqlite3) need Python for compilation. Switched to sql.js — a pure JavaScript SQLite that works without any build tools.</li>
<li><strong>Restricted PowerShell:</strong> Execution policy blocked npm scripts. Had to call npm via full path (<code>C:\Program Files\nodejs\npm.cmd</code>) instead of just <code>npm</code>.</li>
<li><strong>Windows curl + JSON:</strong> PowerShell's single quotes don't parse properly with curl's <code>-d</code> flag. Had to write JSON to a temp file and use <code>-d @file</code> instead.</li>
<li><strong>Multer body timing:</strong> Body fields weren't available in Multer's diskStorage destination callback. Switched to memoryStorage + manual write after validation.</li>
<li><strong>Google Fonts in production build:</strong> Vite doesn't process external CSS imports from node_modules. Used system font stack as fallback.</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>Technologies Used</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Tool</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
<tr><td>Node.js / Express</td><td>Backend server + REST API</td></tr>
<tr><td>React 19 + Vite</td><td>Frontend UI + build tool</td></tr>
<tr><td>SQLite (sql.js)</td><td>Default database (files stored as BLOBs)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Multer</td><td>File upload handling + validation</td></tr>
<tr><td>Git + GitHub</td><td>Version control</td></tr>
</table>

